            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Position, Velocity and Acceleration Continuity</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Finite, but four Jerk discontinuities.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Motion-Law Coefficients</text></para>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Velocity Coefficient: </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">C</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">v</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true"> = 1.33</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Acceleration Coefficient: </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">C</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">a</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">= 8.378</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Jerk Coefficient: </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">C</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">j</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">= ±105.276</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Jerk at Cross-Over 0.25 </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="mailto:&lt;%LINK_CAPTION%&gt;" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Cross-over@0.25</link><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> q: </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">C</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">j(co)</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">=</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true"> ±105.276 (Effectively)</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><text styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" translate="true">Application Notes:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Dynamic Performance</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">This Motion-Law is recommended in applications where you need the peak velocity to be low when compared to others. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">It has a large Peak Acceleration, with a short duration, thus more likely to induce vibrations.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Pressure Angle Considerations</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">It gives a relatively low pressure angle - because of its low peak velocity.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Drive Torques</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">This Motion-Law is not recommended in many applications as it will give a sudden change in torque. The input transmission rigidity would need to be high.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
